 :tx/rationale "ADR-024 OBSERVATION 8: VERBOSE-REQUEST AS TRAINING SIGNAL. When the LLM runs 'braid status --verbose' after seeing compressed output, it's telling us EXACTLY which omitted blocks it needed. This is a zero-noise, zero-cost training signal for the attention weights. The 'verbose after compressed' pattern = direct feedback that the omission was WRONG. Similarly, when the LLM IGNORES a high-attention-score block and acts on a low-score one, the scores were wrong. Every LLM action after a braid output is an implicit calibration data point. The Hebbian rule: strengthen blocks that precede productive actions, weaken blocks that precede unproductive actions or verbose requests."
